law.text: Any person who willfully violates any of the provisions of KRS 197.200 to 197.250 for which no other penalty is herein provided, shall be fined not less than ten dollars ($10) nor more than five hundred dollars ($500), or confined in jail for not less than ten (10) days nor more than one (1) year, or both.
law.history: Repealed in part 1968 Ky. Acts ch. 152, sec. 168. -- Created 1954 Ky. Acts ch. 46, sec. 8.
